                  , to whom he was <rs id="t18280911-393-deflabel2044" type="occupation">servant</rs>
                     <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-393-defend2106 t18280911-393-deflabel2044"></join>
               
                  </rs>.</p>
               <p>JOHN GREEN WINTER. I am in partnership with my brother Robert: we are <rs id="t18280911-393-viclabel2045" type="occupation">cheesemongers</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-393-victim2107 t18280911-393-viclabel2045"></join>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-393-victim2108 t18280911-393-viclabel2045"></join> - the prisoner was in our employ; on the 8th of September I sent him behind the counter while I wrote a letter - during that time the till was robbed; when the prisoner came the next day, I accused him of this felony - he was given in charge, and I went to his house, where I found a butter firkin, and four butter cloths, which are my property, and some flats which are not mine.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-393-person2109">
                  MARGARET 
                  HEWSON
               <interp inst="t18280911-393-person2109" type="surname" value="HEWSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-393-person2109" type="given" value="MARGARET"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-393-person2109" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am servant to Mr. Winter. On the 15th of August, I was coming down stairs - I looked into the warehouse, and saw the prisoner put some ham and a Dutch cheese in a flat; he brought down the flat, and put it into the cart, and took it to the stable - I came down and asked the prisoner if the meat was bad; he said, "What do you mean" - I said, "Never mind," and I stood there till he took it off</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. Have you a fellow-servant named Betsey? A. Yes, she had a sweetheart, but he could not take the prisoner's place - he is not allowed to come to the house; I saw this on the 15th of August - I did not go and tell my master instantly; I did not mention it till the money was gone from the till - some weeks had passed - my master was at home at the time.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-393-person2110">
                  DANIEL 
                  DUTCH
               <interp inst="t18280911-393-person2110" type="surname" value="DUTCH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-393-person2110" type="given" value="DANIEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-393-person2110" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I went with Mr. Winter to the prisoner's lodging, on the 9th of September- I found this butter tub and four cloths; I found no ham or cheese.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Did you take the poor man into custody? A. No, he was at the watch-house; I did not hear his wife say she had taken away some dirty things in the tub.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182809110180"></xptr>MR. WINTER. Hewson told me about taking the ham and cheese on the 8th of September.</p>
               <p>MR. PHILLIPS. Q. Can you swear to the tub? A. Yes, and to these cloths; one of these have a mark on - the prisoner is married; the witness did not say a word to me for some weeks - the prisoner never left my service.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I bought a lot of clothes of the shopman, and took them to the stable, the shopman went with me with some corn; on the Monday I told my wife there was a lot of things I had bought of the shopman - she came to fetch them, but she had no apron on; I said,"Here is a tub, you may take them in that."</p>
               <p>JOHN GREEN WINTER re-examined. Q. Did the prisoner say this at the time? A. No; he was in custody; the tub was filled with cut up flats at the time I found it; he has been five or six months in my service as carman.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18280911-393-verdict2046" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280911-393-verdict2046" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               NOT GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
